Share an Image of a Dashboard Widget on Chatter in Lightning Experience

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISONS NEEDED
To share images of dashboard widgets on Chatter:
 Run Reports
View a dashboard.
Find the widget that you want to share, and expand it by clicking .
In the expanded widget, click .
The Chatter menu opens. You can compose your post and view the dashboard feed by scrolling down.
Compose your post. You can @mention people and groups, and format with rich text.
Click Share.

The dashboard widget image posts to the Dashboard feed. To view the dashboard feed, and your post, click .

NOTE If you canâ€™t post images of dashboard widgets on Chatter, ask your Salesforce admin to turn on feed tracking for dashboards.

Downloaded and shared images of dashboard widget tables can be up to 3000 pixels in height or approximately 100 rows. Rows beyond the limit are clipped. To avoid clipping, filter the chart to fewer than 100 rows.
title: Sharing Dashboard Images on Chatter in Salesforce
